ğŸ¯ Interview-ready answer (perfect)

Concurrency limits protect system resources by restricting parallel execution, but without rate limits a user can still enqueue an unbounded number of jobs and monopolize the system over time. Rate limiting controls queue growth and fairness, while concurrency controls runtime load.

Say this and stop talking. Interviewers love it.

âš™ï¸ Sidekiq Enterprise (clean solution)
sidekiq_options rate: { limit: 5, period: 1.minute }

limiter = Sidekiq::Limiter.concurrent("reports:user:#{user_id}", 1)


Zero custom code. Zero bugs.

